# Cursor Rules — localgov_bus_data Drupal Module

## Project

Drupal 10/11 custom module `localgov_bus_data` for Cumberland Council UK bus timetables.
Data source: BODS API (GTFS timetables + SIRI-VM real-time).
See SPEC.md for full phased delivery plan and architecture decisions.

- Module path: `web/modules/custom/localgov_bus_data/`
- DDEV site: `https://lgd-bus-data-dev.ddev.site` (PHP 8.3, nginx-fpm)
- Stack: Drupal 10.2+, LocalGov Drupal (LGD), Key module, Guzzle

## Agent Resources

Use these proactively — do not wait to be asked:

- **drupal-reviewer** — run after EVERY Drupal PHP file is written or modified. Catches security,
  DI violations, render escaping gaps, and best-practice issues PHPCS will not catch.
- **drupal-expert** — use when uncertain about the correct Drupal API, hook, pattern, or contrib
  option before writing non-trivial Drupal code.
- **ddev-expert** — use when troubleshooting DDEV container, config, or service problems.

## Running Commands

Always use DDEV from the repo root. Never run php/drush/composer directly.

```bash
ddev drush <command>
ddev composer <command>
```

## PHP Standards

- PHP 8.3: typed properties, constructor property promotion, `declare(strict_types=1)` in every file
- `final` on service and form classes unless inheritance is required
- PHP Attributes for plugins: `#[Block(...)]`, `#[Action(...)]` — never `@Block` docblock annotations
- Dependency injection always; never `\Drupal::service()` inside a class
- Exception: static Batch API callbacks may use `\Drupal::service()` — document the reason

## Drupal Patterns

- Config schema required for every custom config key (`config/schema/localgov_bus_data.schema.yml`)
- API keys stored in Key module entities (`drupal/key`), never in plain config
- Cache metadata on all render arrays: `#cache` with appropriate tags, contexts, max-age
- XSS: use `#plain_text` or `Xss::filterAdmin()` for user content; never raw `#markup`
- SQL: parameterized queries only; never concatenate user input

## AJAX Form Rule

Service properties injected into form classes must be `protected` (not `private`/`readonly`).
`DependencySerializationTrait::__sleep()` runs in `FormBase` scope and uses `get_object_vars()`,
which cannot see `private` child-class properties. Do not override `__sleep()`.

AJAX callbacks must build their response element directly on `$form` before returning it.
Do not use `$form_state->setRebuild(TRUE)` inside a callback to add result elements —
the rebuild happens after the callback returns.

## Drush Commands

- Register commands in `drush.services.yml` (Drush reads this, NOT `services.yml`).
- Also register in `services.yml` (without `drush.command` tag) so the class is available as
  a Drupal service for cron hooks and Batch API callbacks.
- Mark the `services.yml` entry `lazy: true` — it is a CLI-only service.

## BODS API Notes

- Base URL: `https://data.bus-data.dft.gov.uk/api/v1`
- Auth: `?api_key=<value>` query param (key from Key module entity)
- Repeated query params (e.g. `adminArea=080&adminArea=081`): build manually with
  `http_build_query` + string concat. Guzzle mangles PHP arrays into `adminArea[0]=` format.
- Cumberland NaPTAN admin area codes: `080` (Copeland), `081` (Allerdale), `082` (Carlisle)
- Cumberland bounding box: N:55.10 S:54.15 E:-2.45 W:-3.75

## GTFS Filter

`GtfsFilter` service trims downloads to the configured bounding box.
Trip IDs are the pivot — all stop_times and stops for qualifying trips are kept,
including out-of-box stops on cross-boundary routes (e.g. Carlisle→Gretna).
Processing is line-by-line (`fgetcsv`/`fputcsv`); never load full GTFS files into memory.

## Phase Status

- Phase 1 (Foundation): complete
- Phase 2 (Data import): complete — five content entities, Drush import command, cron, import log
- Phases 3–6: see SPEC.md

## Prefer Contrib

Before writing custom code, check drupal.org for an existing contrib module.
